urls.title: Eagle, Steller's Sea - Louisville Zoo
urls.description: RANGE: Breed in eastern Russia, around the Sea of Okhotsk and on the Kamchatka Peninsula. A small number of birds remain in Kamchatka over the winter but the majority fly south to the Japanese Islands of Kuril and Hokkaido. This species is occasionally seen in China and in North & South Korea. HABITAT: Mostly found on sea coasts or along large rivers not far inland. STATUS: Vulnerable Find Out More

text:
It's #NationalSaveTheEaglesDay! The Steller's sea eagles are on average the heaviest species of eagle, however despite their size and power they still face many threats to their habitats in eastern Russia and Japan.
